Healthcare workers waiting to administer Pfizer vaccines. eNCA/Heidi Giokos JOHANNESBURG - The National Institute for Communicable Diseases (NICD) has reported 9,757 new COVID-19 infections. A further seven people have died from COVID-19 related deaths Meanwhile, the Department of Health backtracked on the face mask mandate in schools on Wednesday. READ: Pupils to continue wearing masks in classrooms It now says children in schools must continue complying with wearing face masks in classrooms and indoor gatherings. The department has extended the public consultation period for health regulation amendments until 5 July. #COVID19 UPDATE: 37,618 tests were conducted in the last 24hrs, with 9,757 new cases, which represents a 25.9% positivity rate. Today @HealthZA reports 64 deaths; of which 7 occurred in the past 24–48 hrs. Total fatalities are 100,471 to date: https://t.co/1cExD4h5bZ pic.twitter.com/haOSRPCHNA